Schmallenberg virus, Belgium: Immediate Notification
----------------------------------------------------
Information received on 12 Jan 2012 from Dr. Pierre Naassens, Directeur Sante des Animaux et Securite des Produits animaux/ CVO, Direction Sante des Animaux et Securite des Produits animaux, Agence Federale pour la Securite de la Chaine Alimentaire, Bruxelles, Belgium

Summary
Report type: Immediate notification
Start date: 14 Dec 2011
Date of 1st confirmation of the event: 06 Jan 2012
Report date: 12 Jan 2012
Date submitted to OIE: 12 Jan 2012
Reason for notification: Emerging disease
Morbidity: 3.5 percent
Mortality: 3.5 percent
Zoonotic impact: No
Causal agent: Schmallenberg virus [SBV]

New outbreaks: [For the names, dates and population data regarding the 14 locations where sheep holdings are reported as affected, please go to the source URL. A map is included. - Mod.AS]

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 14
Total animals affected:
Species/ Susceptible/ Cases/ Deaths
Sheep/758 /27 /27

Outbreak statistics:
Species/Apparent morbidity rate/Apparent mortality rate/Apparent case fatality rate/
Sheep/ 3.56 percent/ 3.56 percent/ 100.00 percent

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Unknown or inconclusive; Vectors

Control measures
Measures applied: No vaccination; No treatment of affected animals

Measures to be applied: No other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Veterinary and Agrochemical Research Centre (CERVA) (National laboratory)
Tests and results
Species/ Test/ Test date/ Result
Sheep/ real-time reverse transcriptase -- polymerase chain reaction (RRT-PCR)/ 06 Jan 2012/ Positive

